title: ‘Ruthless’ Prince William enforces strict ‘zero tolerance’ approach following Andrew scandal
description: UK barrister and broadcaster Andrew Eborn discusses Prince William and Princess Catherine enforcing a strict “zero-tolerance” approach as Prince Andrew deals with multiple scandals involving links to Jeffrey Epstein.  “Prince William is being quite ruthless about this. He doesn’t want anyone to tarnish the crown,” he told Sky News Digital Presenter Gabriella Power.  “And that’s exactly what all these headlines [are] screaming every single day.”

title: Sky News host mocks AOC’s unhinged rant
description: Sky News host Rita Panahi mocked Democrat Representative Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez for an unhinged rant she gave in support of New York City mayoral candidate Zohran Mamdani.

title: Chuck Schumer blocks GOP bid to re-open US government for the 13th time
description: Senate Minority Leader Chuck Schumer has blasted Republicans in Congress for "doing nothing" to reopen the government.  The vote marks the 13th failed attempt to reopen the government after a series of pressure-point deadlines had rapidly closed in.  Failure to reopen the government again came as air traffic controllers missed their first payday.  The near-month-long shutdown has also significantly affected air travel, creating flight delays and staffing shortages.

title: Sky News host reacts to the media's obsession with Trump seeking a third term
description: Sky News host Rita Panahi, joined by Sky News contributor Kosha Gada, addresses the media's obsession with the ridiculous notion that Trump will seek a third term.

title: ‘Purge the pomp’: Prince William plans to scrap ‘ridiculous’ and ‘outdated’ royal traditions
description: UK barrister and broadcaster Andrew Eborn has commented on Prince William’s plan to scrap “ridiculous” and “totally outdated” royal traditions when he becomes king.  “He’s going to purge the pomp,” he told Sky News Digital Presenter Gabriella Power.  “A stronger emphasis on purpose is what he wants.”

title: ‘Just not going away’: Prince Andrew now faces a ‘tsunami of scandals’ as Epstein links deepen
description: Prince Andrew is facing a “tsunami of scandals” which is “just not going away” as more and more revelations are revealed, according to UK barrister and broadcaster Andrew Eborn.  “It’s a tsunami of scandals which is just not going away,” he told Sky News Digital Presenter Gabriella Power.  “It’s getting bigger if anything.”

title: Health Minister lashes out at Sussan Ley over Medicare bulk-billing
description: Health Minister Mark Butler lashes out at Opposition leader Sussan Ley for her previous role as health minister.  “The only health minister in the history of Medicare never once to increase the Medicare rebate,” he said during Question Time on Tuesday.  “Marking herself out as the person probably most responsible for the situation we inherited.  “A situation with bulk-billing in freefall.”

title: Nigel Farage slams ‘terrifying’ masked protesters after chaos breaks out on London streets
description: Reform UK leader Nigel Farage has blasted a group of masked protesters who took over the streets of Tower Hamlets in East London, dressed in entirely black clothing including balaclavas and chanting in Arabic in a bid to reclaim the area.

title: Andrew hosted Epstein, Maxwell, and Weinstein at Royal Lodge after US arrest warrant was issued
description: It’s been revealed that Prince Andrew hosted Jeffrey Epstein, Ghislaine Maxwell, and Harvey Weinstein at Royal Lodge, the prince’s private home in the grounds of Windsor Castle.  Prince Andrew is facing a “tsunami of scandals” which is “just not going away” as more and more revelations are revealed, according to UK barrister and broadcaster Andrew Eborn.  “This was two months after the US arrest warrant had been issued for Epstein,” he told Sky News Digital Presenter Gabriella Power.

title: ‘She’ll have a glorious time’: Princess Anne to tour Australia and Singapore with her husband
description: UK barrister and broadcaster Andrew Eborn discusses Princess Anne and her husband Tim Laurence’s expected long-haul royal visit to Australia and Singapore in November.  “It’s going to be the 100th anniversary ... of the Royal Australian Corps of Signals,” he told Sky News Digital Presenter Gabriella Power.  “She’s one of the favourite royals over here; she works incredibly hard, but she’ll have a glorious time there.”

title: King Charles attempts to escape Andrew drama as he makes history praying with Pope Leo
description: UK barrister and broadcaster Andrew Eborn has commented on King Charles and Pope Leo making history after praying together in the Vatican’s Sistine Chapel.  “He made history,” he told Sky News Digital Presenter Gabriella Power.  “Incredibly dramatic pictures in the Sistine Chapel. They were praying side by side. A first for the leaders of the Church of England and the Catholic Church.  “He [King Charles] wanted to try and get away, if you like, from the Prince Andrew scandal.”

title: ‘More explosions, more scandals’: Fears Fergie could ‘go rogue’ and air royal secrets if exiled
description: UK barrister and broadcaster Andrew Eborn discusses growing fears that Sarah Ferguson could “go rogue” and start airing secrets of the Royal Family if she and Prince Andrew are exiled from royal life.  “Sarah Ferguson now is looking to do a tell-all memoir, and it’s not the first one she did,” he told Sky News Digital Presenter Gabriella Power.  “More explosions; more scandals.  “If she’s strapped for cash, she could be very, very tempted to do it, so do watch this space.”

title: Meghan Markle left ‘shaken’ by Victoria Beckham’s latest move as bitter ‘rivalry’ deepens
description: UK barrister and broadcaster Andrew Eborn discusses the bitter “rivalry” between Meghan Markle and Victoria Beckham deepening.  Mr Eborn claimed Meghan Markle is “shaken” by the success of Ms Beckham’s latest Netflix documentary.  “There is that rivalry,” Mr Eborn told Sky News Digital Presenter Gabriella Power.

title: Meghan Markle ‘reeling’ over Victoria Beckham’s latest success
description: Sky News Digital Presenter Gabriella Power claims Meghan Markle is apparently “reeling” after her former friend Victoria Beckham’s latest success put her own efforts under renewed scrutiny.  “Of course, Meghan’s not all that happy about Victoria Beckham’s latest Netflix documentary, and she’s apparently shaken by it because of the success around Victoria Beckham’s documentary,” she said.  “It’s certainly seen as a much bigger success than ‘With Love, Meghan’.”

title: Jim Chalmers accuses Sussan Ley of ‘opposing’ Labor’s cost of living relief policies
description: Treasurer Jim Chalmers accused the Coalition of opposing Labor’s “efforts” to decrease cost-of-living pressures for Australians during Question Time on Wednesday.  “If the Opposition leader really cared about cost-of-living pressures, she wouldn’t have just gone to an election promising to increase taxes on every single tax-paying Australian worker,” Mr Chalmers said.  “If they cared about cost of living, they wouldn’t oppose our efforts to provide responsible cost-of-living relief.”
